"configurado para la generación de texto."

#: src/Admin/WithdrawalSettingsPage.php:311
msgid "Not available."
msgstr "No disponible."

#: src/Admin/WithdrawalSettingsPage.php:312
msgid ""
"Install WordPress 7.0 or higher and at least one AI Client provider plugin "
"(for example Vercel AI Gateway, AI Provider for Anthropic, AI Provider for "
"Google, or AI Provider for OpenAI) to enable AI augmentation."
msgstr ""
"Instale WordPress 7.0 o superior y al menos un complemento de proveedor de "
"AI Client (por ejemplo, Vercel AI Gateway, AI Provider for Anthropic, AI "
"Provider for Google o AI Provider for OpenAI) para habilitar el aumento de "
"AI."

#: src/Admin/WithdrawalSettingsPage.php:318
msgid "Classify withdrawal reasons"
msgstr "Clasificar los motivos de retiro"

#: src/Admin/WithdrawalSettingsPage.php:328
msgid ""
"Ask the AI Client to classify the free-text reason on every new withdrawal "
"into one of a fixed set of categories (defective, wrong item, size mismatch,"
" changed mind, late delivery, damaged in transit, not as described, other)."
msgstr ""
"Solicite al Cliente de AI que clasifique el motivo del texto libre en cada "
"nuevo retiro en una de un conjunto fijo de categorías (defectuoso, artículo "
"incorrecto, discrepancia de tamaño, cambio de opinión, entrega tardía, "
"dañado durante el transporte, no como se describe, otro)."

#: src/Admin/WithdrawalSettingsPage.php:331
msgid ""
"Disabled by default. No outbound HTTP request is ever made by this plugin; "
"the AI Client provider plugin you install handles the network call. "
"Classification runs silently in the background after a customer or operator "
"files a declaration; failures (no provider, prevented prompt, network error)"
" are absorbed and never block the withdrawal flow."
msgstr ""
"Deshabilitado por defecto. Este complemento nunca realiza ninguna solicitud "
"HTTP saliente; el complemento del proveedor AI Client que instale maneja la "
"llamada de red. La clasificación se ejecuta silenciosamente en segundo plano"
" después de que un cliente u operador presenta una declaración; Las fallas "
"(ausencia de proveedor, aviso impedido, error de red) se absorben y nunca "
"bloquean el flujo de retiro."

